&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;THIS POST IS FIXED TERM UNTIL 31/03/2022 DUE TO MEET THE NEEDS OF THE SERVICE.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for dynamic, innovative and highly motivated Advanced Analyst Modeller to join the Velindre Trust to lead and support analytical and modelling projects and reporting across the Velindre and South East Wales Cancer Services.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;The post holder will report directly to the Head of Information within Velindre Cancer Centre and duties will include:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;Creating simulation, statistical and planning models that generate insight into services and directly support operational service planning and delivery&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;Supporting a variety of diverse modelling and capacity planning projects across Velindre and NHS Wales&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;Facilitating technical modelling discussions and supporting training with non-technical operational colleagues and stakeholders &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;Manage the Corporate Analysis and Reporting Service, including areas such as, performance reporting.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;The ideal candidate will have experience of applying operational research, modelling, analytical and statistical theory in an NHS environment.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;The successful candidate will have the opportunity to be part of developing and achieving sustainable improvement to patient care through whole system approach to service planning and delivery. The candidate will gain experience in different setting within the Trust and across NHS Wales through collaborate working with organisation such as DU, Improvement Cymru, Cancer Network and Health Boards. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;The ability to speak Welsh is desirable for this post; English and/or Welsh speakers are equally welcome to apply&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Closing date: 23rd November 2020&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Name: Emma Powell&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Job title: Head of Information &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Email address: Emma.Powell@wales.nhs.uk&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
